        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 5:53PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 552 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Rising Sun,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Cincinnati, Covington, Florence, Independence, Erlanger, Edgewood,
Elsmere, Fort Mitchell, Villa Hills, Fort Wright, Crescent Springs,
Aurora, Crestview Hills, Lakeside Park, Rising Sun, Oakbrook,
Burlington, Union, French, and Richwood.

This includes I-75 in Kentucky between mile markers 175 and 186.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
